of
disquiet
and
misery
. Read then this
spotless
book. There you will learn to love
those
of
our faith, and not hate
those
of any other.
You will learn the
necessity
of being
virtuous
here, that you may be happy and not
miserable
hereafter. You will learn
refignation
to the will of the Holy One;
because
you will know, that all the events
of your life were, in the embryo of time,
forged on the anvils of Divine
Wisdom
.
In a word, you will learn the unity of
God, which,
notwithstanding
the cavil of
your divines, your prophet, like ours, came
into the world to
establish
, and every man
of
reason
must
believe. You need not
renounce your prophet. Him we
respect
F 2
as a great
apostle
of God; but
Mahomet
is the
seal
of the prophets. Turn
then, my friend, from
slavery
to the
delights
of life. Throw off the
shackles
of
education from your
